# Cyfrin PasswordStore Security Analysis

## Overview

This write-up analyzes vulnerabilities found in the **Cyfrin PasswordStore** smart contract.  
The contract attempts to store and manage a password on-chain, but contains critical design and access control flaws.

---

# [H-1] Storing Password On-Chain Makes It Publicly Visible

## Description

All data stored on-chain is publicly accessible.  
Even if a variable is marked as `private` in Solidity, it does **not** make it secret at the blockchain level.

